music.originalTitle: Khush Mohammad Farkhari     Muqam e Farkhar
music.title: Khush Mohammad Farkhari     Muqam e Farkhar
remember you maid
music.description:
Text: Jónas Hallgrímsson (1807 - 1845).
Tune: trad., arr. Bára Grímsdóttir & Chris Foster.
A love song by Iceland’s 'national poet', set to a traditional tvísöngur tune and accompanied on langspil, which sometimes takes the line of the second voice. Regular use of the Icelandic langspil ceased about a hundred years ago, sadly before any recordings could be made. A revival is definitely long overdue.

music.title: Marewrew - Sa Oy
music.description:
Marewrew is a group of four women working on diffusion and renewal of the ancient Upopo songs of the Ainu people.
Originally based in Northern Japan (Hokkaido island), Sakhalin and the Kuril Islands, the Ainu have been oppressed in both Japan and Russia, and their cultural characteristics (language, art, shamanism) are facing a complex and dangerous situation.
